dct_description_sm: Prepared by the Army Map Service (GE), Corps of Engineers, U. S. Army, Washington D.C. , original map compiled by US Geological Survey. Alternate title: Indiana 1:25,000. Filing title: Bippus, Indiana : Huntington County. Standard map series designation: AMS (Series) V851 Sheet 3865 I NE. Edition 1--AMS. Transverse Mercator projection. Army Map Service , V851. Relief shown by contours and spot heights. Shows roads, railroads, boundaries, buildings, mines, and natural features. Marginal maps: Index to boundaries -- Index to adjoining sheets. Contour interval 10 feet. "Copied in 1959 from Indiana, 1:24,000, USGS, Bippus, 1955. Original map compiled by U.S. Geological Survey. Culture and drainage in part compiled from aerial photographs taken 1948. Topography by planetable methods, 1950 and 1955. Horizontal and vertical control by USGS and USC&GS. ... Scale changed, Universal Transverse Mercator Grid added, marginal data revised, 1959." "First Printing, 11-59." "Printed by Army Map Service, Corps of Engineers, 11-59." Printed with vegetation.
Imprint: Washington, D.C. : Army Map Service, Corps of Engineers, 1959.
Dimensions: 56 x 45 cm or smaller; Scale: 1:25,000
dct_creator_sm: Geological Survey (U.S.); United States. Army Map Service
